{"title":"Warding","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Warding","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n**Warding** is an [intrinsic](/Intrinsic \"Intrinsic\") that sometimes causes the melee and ranged weapon attacks of summoned monsters against you to fail:\n\n> *(Monster) tries to attack you, but flinches away.*\n\nThe chance of the attack being prevented is based on the monster's [magic resistance](/Magic_resistance \"Magic resistance\"). Each attack forces a roll of the monster's MR vs. 1d60; if the monster's roll wins, the attack goes through as normal.\n\nHowever, it will not prevent summoned monsters from casting [spells](/Spell \"Spell\") or using abilities such as [torment](/Torment \"Torment\") or [hellfire](/Hellfire \"Hellfire\") against you. This makes it much more useful against such spells as [Summon Horrible Things](/Summon_Horrible_Things \"Summon Horrible Things\") and [Haunt](/Haunt \"Haunt\") than against [Summon Greater Demon](/Summon_Greater_Demon \"Summon Greater Demon\"), for example.\n\nWarding will not provide protection against monsters that are [durably summoned](/Durably_summoned \"Durably summoned\").\n\nWarding can be obtained through:\n\n- [Amulet of warding](/Amulet_of_warding \"Amulet of warding\")\n- [Staff of summoning](/Staff_of_summoning \"Staff of summoning\")\n- [Macabre finger necklace](/Macabre_finger_necklace \"Macabre finger necklace\")\n- Some [randarts](/Randart \"Randart\")\n\n## History\n\n- Removed in [0.18](/0.18 \"0.18\").\n- Prior to [0.17](/0.17 \"0.17\"), warding didn't apply to ranged attacks.\n- Prior to [0.11](/0.11 \"0.11\"), you could have up to two ranks of warding by wearing an amulet of warding while wielding a [staff of summoning](/Staff_of_summoning \"Staff of summoning\"). Each rank of the old warding intrinsic was worth half of what current warding provides.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html